verbs.description: A bipartisan group of 10 senators [V: has] introduced legislation that challenges the Trump administration on its effort to punish trading partners in the name of national security . The senators want to push legislation that would require Congress to approve of such tariffs , though passing such a bill is a longshot . GOP lawmakers are mostly at odds with what they view as President Donald Trump 's protectionist instincts on trade . But many also hesitate to anger his supporters in an election year .
